<span id="freeTextContainer13813836995729688981">I read this one for class so I didn’t truly read every word lol but I thought this was a pretty compelling argument. Basically everything in politics depends on the amount of people in the winning coalition, AKA the people who decide who is in power. In a democracy its a lot more people that need to be pleased to maintain power and authoritarians only need to pay off a few individuals to stay in power. Pretty interesting and solid case studies to support I thought. In this cynical view though th</span>
  <span id="freeText13813836995729688981" style="display:none">I read this one for class so I didn’t truly read every word lol but I thought this was a pretty compelling argument. Basically everything in politics depends on the amount of people in the winning coalition, AKA the people who decide who is in power. In a democracy its a lot more people that need to be pleased to maintain power and authoritarians only need to pay off a few individuals to stay in power. Pretty interesting and solid case studies to support I thought. In this cynical view though the only thing that matters to leaders is staying in power which i think (or I hope) isnt the case. just the underinformed opinion of a girl desperately trying to finish her reading challenge /:</span>
